Creating pitch classifications from Trackman data at Kinetic Performance Institute

library(readxl)
library(ggplot2)

# import necessary data
pitchdata <- read_excel("pitcheralldata_copy.xlsx", skip = 2)


# keep only necessary variables
pitchdata <- select(pitchdata, 1, 2, 5, 6, 8, 9, 11, 14, 15, 16, 21)


# remove observations with NA:
pitchdata <- pitchdata[complete.cases(pitchdata), ]


#change names of columns:
names(pitchdata) <- c("hb", "pitchtype", "velo", "spinrate", "rheight", "rside", "tilt", "spineff", "vaa", "haa", "vb")


# convert tilt to degrees:
tilt <- c("12:00", "12:15", "12:30", "12:45", "1:00", "1:15", "1:30", "1:45",
          "2:00", "2:15", "2:30", "2:45", "3:00", "3:15", "3:30", "3:45",
          "4:00", "4:15", "4:30", "4:45", "5:00", "5:15", "5:30", "5:45",
          "6:00", "6:15", "6:30", "6:45", "7:00", "7:15", "7:30", "7:45",
          "8:00", "8:15", "8:30", "8:45", "9:00", "9:15", "9:30", "9:45",
          "10:00", "10:15", "10:30", "10:45", "11:00", "11:15", "11:30", "11:45")

time_to_degrees <- function(time) {
  time_split <- as.numeric(unlist(strsplit(time, ":")))
  hour <- time_split[1]
  minute <- time_split[2]
  
  # Calculate angle from 12 o'clock position
  angle <- (hour %% 12) * 30 + (minute / 2)
  
  # Adjust for opposite sides of the clock
  if (angle > 180) {
    angle <- 360 - angle
  }
  
  return(angle)
}

pitchdata$dtilt <- sapply(pitchdata$tilt, time_to_degrees)

pitchdata <- select(pitchdata, -tilt)


# remove undefined pitches
pitchdata <- pitchdata %>% 
  filter(pitchtype != "Undefined")


# create datasets for each pitch
fastballdata <- pitchdata %>%
  filter(pitchtype == "Fastball")

changeupdata <- pitchdata %>%
  filter(pitchtype == "ChangeUp")

breakerdata <- pitchdata %>%
  filter(pitchtype == "Slider" | pitchtype == "Curveball")


# normalizing fastball data for RHP
fastballdata$hb <- abs(fastballdata$hb)

# normalizing changeup data for RHP
changeupdata$hb <- abs(changeupdata$hb)

# normalizing breaker data for RHP
breakerdata$hb <- abs(breakerdata$hb) * -1
breakerdata$haa <- abs(breakerdata$haa) * -1


# classifying & plotting fastballs
risingfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 17 & hb <= 8)

traditional4seamfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 15 & hb >= 8 & hb <= 15)

superhybridfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 15 & hb >= 15)

gyrobackspinfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 17 & dtilt >= 0 & dtilt <= 30)

gyrohybridfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb < 15 & hb < 15 & dtilt >= 30 & dtilt <= 60)

runningfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 8 & vb <= 15 & hb >= 15)

sinkingfastball <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 8 & hb >= 16)

gyrosinker <- fastballdata %>%
  filter(hb <= 16 & dtilt >= 60)

filteredfastballs <- bind_rows(risingfastball, traditional4seamfastball, superhybridfastball, gyrobackspinfastball, gyrohybridfastball, runningfastball, sinkingfastball, gyrosinker)
leftoverfastballs <- fastballdata %>%
  anti_join(filteredfastballs)
## Joining with `by = join_by(hb, pitchtype, velo, spinrate, rheight, rside,
## spineff, vaa, haa, vb, dtilt)`
# classifying changeups/splitters
backspinchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 16 & hb <= 10)

hybridchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 13 & hb >= 10)

gyrobackspinchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 16 & dtilt >= 0 & dtilt <= 30)

runningchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 7 & vb <= 13 & hb >= 15)

gyrochange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 15 & hb <= 15 & dtilt >= 30 & dtilt <= 60)

fadingchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 7 & hb >= 14)

gyrofadingchange <- changeupdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 7 & hb <= 14 & dtilt >= 60)

filteredchangeups <- bind_rows(backspinchange, hybridchange, gyrobackspinchange, runningchange, gyrochange, fadingchange, gyrofadingchange)
leftoverchangeups <- changeupdata %>%
  anti_join(filteredchangeups)
## Joining with `by = join_by(hb, pitchtype, velo, spinrate, rheight, rside,
## spineff, vaa, haa, vb, dtilt)`
# classifying breakers
backupbreaker <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb > 0 & hb > 0)

traditionalcutter <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 7 & hb >= -6 & hb <= 0)

slutter <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 4 & vb <= 7 & hb >= -6 & hb <= 0)

gyroslider <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb <= 5 & vb >= -4 & hb >= -5 & hb <= 0)

traditionalslider <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= -4 & vb <= 5 & hb >= -12 & hb <= -5)

sweeper <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= -4 & vb <= 5 & hb <= -12)

slurve <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= -8 & vb <= -4 & hb <= -15)

gyrocurveball <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= -12 & vb <= -4 & hb >= -15 & hb <= -7)

traditionalcurveball <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb <= -10 & hb >= -15 & hb <= -5)

inefficientdowner <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= -12 & vb <= -4 & hb >= -7)

twelvesix <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb <= -12 & hb >= -7)

ridingslutter <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb >= 5 & hb <= -5)

bigcurveball <- breakerdata %>%
  filter(vb <= -8 & hb <= -15)

filteredbreakers <- bind_rows(backupbreaker, traditionalcutter, slutter, gyroslider, traditionalslider, sweeper, slurve, gyrocurveball, traditionalcurveball, inefficientdowner, twelvesix, ridingslutter, bigcurveball)
leftoverbreakers <- breakerdata %>%
  anti_join(filteredbreakers)
## Joining with `by = join_by(hb, pitchtype, velo, spinrate, rheight, rside,
## spineff, vaa, haa, vb, dtilt)`
# model for inputting metrics and outputting pitch type


# plotting different pitches
combinedfastballs <- bind_rows(risingfastball %>% mutate(type = "rising fastball"),
                               traditional4seamfastball %>% mutate(type = "traditional 4seam fastball"),
                               superhybridfastball %>% mutate(type = "super hybrid fastball"),
                               gyrobackspinfastball %>% mutate(type = "gyro backspin fastball"),
                               gyrohybridfastball %>% mutate(type = "gyro hybrid fastball"),
                               runningfastball %>% mutate(type = "running fastball"),
                               sinkingfastball %>% mutate(type = "sinking fastball"),
                               gyrosinker %>% mutate(type = "gyro sinker"),
                               .id = "dataset")
ggplot(combinedfastballs, aes(x = hb, y = vb, color = type)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Fastballs",
       x = "Horizontal Break",
       y = "Vertical Break",
       color = "Type of Fastball") +
  theme_minimal()

combinedchangeups <- bind_rows(backspinchange %>% mutate(type = "backspin change"),
                               hybridchange %>% mutate(type = "hybrid change"),
                               gyrobackspinchange %>% mutate(type = "gyro backspin change"),
                               runningchange %>% mutate(type = "running change"),
                               gyrochange %>% mutate(type = "gyro change"),
                               fadingchange %>% mutate(type = "fading change"),
                               gyrofadingchange %>% mutate(type = "gyro fading change"),
                               .id = "dataset")
ggplot(combinedchangeups, aes(x = hb, y = vb, color = type)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Changeups",
       x = "Horizontal Break",
       y = "Vertical Break",
       color = "Type of Changeup") +
  theme_minimal()

combinedbreakers <- bind_rows(backupbreaker %>% mutate(type = "backup breaker"),
                              traditionalcutter %>% mutate(type = "traditional cutter"),
                              slutter %>% mutate(type = "slutter"),
                              gyroslider %>% mutate(type = "gyro slider"),
                              traditionalslider %>% mutate(type = "traditional slider"),
                              sweeper %>% mutate(type = "sweeper"),
                              slurve %>% mutate(type = "slurve"),
                              gyrocurveball %>% mutate(type = "gyro curveball"),
                              traditionalcurveball %>% mutate(type = "traditional curveball"),
                              inefficientdowner %>% mutate(type = "inefficient downer"),
                              twelvesix %>% mutate(type = "twelve six"),
                              ridingslutter %>% mutate(type = "riding slutter"),
                              bigcurveball %>% mutate(type = "big curveball"),
                              .id = "dataset")
ggplot(combinedbreakers, aes(x = hb, y = vb, color = type)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Breakers",
       x = "Horizontal Break",
       y = "Vertical Break",
